Eni, Generali, Parmalat, Pop. Milano: Italy Equity Preview

-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t   a n d   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 
2011-05-02T06:30:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/eni-generali-parmalat-pop-milano-italy-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  increased 37.77, or 0.2
percent, to 22,417.96 in Milan on April 29.  Assicurazioni Generali SpA (G)  : Italy’s largest insurer
said first-quarter gross premiums fell 8.3 percent, affected by
a contraction of premiums at its life-insurance business.
Generali rose 0.3 percent to 16.18 euros, in its seventh daily
gain.  Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl (PMI IM): General Manager
Fiorenzo Dalu resigned, according to a statement distributed by
the Italian exchange yesterday. The shares lost 0.8 percent to
2.31 euros.  Eni Spa (ENI)  : A sale of Eni SpA’s controlling stake in
 Snam Rete Gas Spa (SRG)   would “weaken” Italy’s biggest
energy company, Chairman Roberto Poli told  Corriere della Sera .
Eni gained 0.7 percent to 18.05 euros. Snam declined 0.14
percent to 4.2 euros.  Parmalat SpA (PLT)  : Consob, Italy’s financial-markets
watchdog, will examine Groupe Lactalis’s bid for Parmalat SpA
“rapidly,” Giuseppe Vegas, the chairman of the regulator, said
in an interview with La Stampa.  Parmalat’s board will meet May 3 to evaluate the offer, Il
Sole 24 reported. Parmalat increased 0.6 percent to 2.56 euros.  Piaggio & C. SpA (PIA IM): Exane BNP Paribas reiterated an
“outperform” rating on the scootermaker saying that quarterly
results were “bang in line” with its expectations. The shares
added 0.7 percent to 2.64 euros.  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  : Chief Executive Officer  Federico
Ghizzoni  said an initial public offering of the Pioneer Global
Asset Management unit is an option. UniCredit rose 0.5 percent
to 1.738 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
